@Jehan To try out the new driver I once again updated to 2.10.8. The driver didn't do anything, and it actually broke the software I need to set up shortcuts and other settings on my tablet - it stopped recognizing my tablet. I had to uninstall it. 

To reiterate, my tablet works in 2.10.6 but not 2.10.8, and this is the first version of GIMP that hasn't worked with my tablet. Moving back to an older version of GIMP than 2.10.8 causes everything to work perfectly again. My tablet is a Gaomon tablet as I said before, not Huion. In 2.10.8, I can move my cursor around and select all tools and menus so I know the tablet is recognized, but I can't draw anything. If I turn off the pressure stylus in Input Devices, I can draw with no pressure. Checking/unchecking "enable windows ink" does not do anything. 

As a final test, after playing with all of these settings and drivers I reinstalled 2.10.6. It works fine again, so it's definitely an issue in 2.10.8 only.

